text="Flexible transclusion options">Flexible transclusion options</fr:title><fr:taxon>Feature</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>This release replaces the old <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude*]]></fr:code>, <fr:code><![CDATA[\transclude@]]></fr:code> commands with a more flexible transclusion configuration mechanism using the support for fluid binding introduced in <fr:link
href="jms-005O.xml"
title="Forester 2.1"
addr="jms-005O"
type="local">Forester 2.1</fr:link>. A basic transclusion with the default options is done in the same way as before:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\transclude{jms-0005}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>The behavior of transclusion is, however, configurable by several globally allocated fluid bindings as depicted in the <fr:link
href="jms-0069.xml"
title="Transclusion options"
addr="jms-0069"
type="local">table below</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:tree
