      \query/author{jonmsterling}
      \query/taxon{reference}
      \query/tag{featured}
    }
  }
}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>Under the hood, a query node is an “anonymous transclusion” and can therefore be <fr:link
href="jms-0067.xml"
title="Forester 2.2 › flexible transclusion options"
addr="jms-0067"
type="local">configured using the same options as other transclusions</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>A minor change is that the <fr:code>assets</fr:code> directly does not need to be flat anymore.</fr:p><fr:p>As always, existing forests can be upgraded by copying <fr:code>forest.xsl</fr:code> and <fr:code>style.css</fr:code> into their <fr:code>assets</fr:code> directory.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
