type="user">jms-00X0</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00X0.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Expressing built-in queries">Expressing built-in queries</fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>The built-in basic queries can be expressed in terms of <fr:link
href="jms-00WY.xml"
title="Forester 4.2 › new query language › relational queries › the syntax of a relational query"
addr="jms-00WY"
type="local"><fr:code><![CDATA[\query/rel]]></fr:code></fr:link> in the following way:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\my-query/author[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\incoming}{\rel/authors}{\x}
}

\def\my-query/taxon[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\incoming}{\rel/taxa}{\x}
}

\def\my-query/tag[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\incoming}{\rel/tags}{\x}
}]]></fr:pre></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>6535</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00X2</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00X2.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Querying the (back)links and context a given tree">Querying the (back)links and context a given tree</fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Both the backlinks and (forward) links of a given tree can be computed using a query to the <fr:code><![CDATA[\rel/links]]></fr:code> relation, and the context (immediate parents) of a given tree can be obatined from the <fr:code><![CDATA[\query/transclusion]]></fr:code> relation:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\query/backlinks[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\incoming}{\rel/links}{\x}
}

\def\query/links[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\outgoing}{\rel/links}{\x}
}

\def\query/context[x]{
 \open\query
 \rel{\edges}{\incoming}{\rel/transclusion}{\x}
}]]></fr:pre></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
