type="user">jms-00X1</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00X1.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Unions and intersections of families of queries">Unions and intersections of families of queries</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A further primitive query-former is the union or intersection of a certain <fr:em>family</fr:em> of queries indexed in the <fr:em>results</fr:em> of a fixed query. These are written as follows:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\query/union-fam{q}{qfam}
\query/isect-fam{q}{qfam}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>In the above, <fr:code>q</fr:code> is a query expression and <fr:code>qfam</fr:code> is a <fr:link
href="jms-00YF.xml"
title="Forester 4.2 › first-class functions and lazy arguments"
addr="jms-00YF"
type="local"><fr:em>first-class function</fr:em></fr:link> that takes an address and returns a query expression. There are a couple built-in instantiations of <fr:code><![CDATA[\query/union-fam]]></fr:code> and <fr:code><![CDATA[\query/isect-fam]]></fr:code> for the specific case where <fr:code>qfam</fr:code> is a family of <fr:em>relational</fr:em> queries; for example:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\query/union-fam-rel{q}{mode}{polarity}{rel}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>is equivalent to the following more verbose code:</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\query/union-fam{q}{
 \fun[x]{
  \query/rel{mode}{pol}{\x}
 }
}]]></fr:pre><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>6538</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">jms-00X3</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00X3.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Querying the bibliography of a given tree">Querying the bibliography of a given tree</fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can define a macro to compute the bibliography of a given tree, making use of <fr:code><![CDATA[\query/transclusion-coslice]]></fr:code> from <fr:link
href="jms-00X4.xml"
title="Forester 4.2 › new query language › relational queries › querying a coslice of the transclusion preorder"
addr="jms-00X4"
type="local">Example <fr:contextual-number
addr="jms-00X4" /></fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\query/bibliography[x]{
 \open\query
 \isect{
  \union-fam-rel{\transclusion-coslice{\x}}{\edges}{\outgoing}{\rel/links}
 }{
  \taxon{reference}
 }
}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>The above code first accumulates all the outgoing links from the given tree and any of its children, and then restricts (by intersection) to those with taxon <fr:code>reference</fr:code>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
