type="user">jms-00X5</fr:addr><fr:route>jms-00X5.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Querying all hereditary contributors to a tree">Querying all hereditary contributors to a tree</fr:title><fr:taxon>Example</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can use the union of families of relational queries to compute the set of (proper) <fr:link
href="tfmt-000T.xml"
title="Contributor to a tree"
addr="tfmt-000T"
type="local"><fr:em>contributors</fr:em></fr:link> to a given tree. This is slightly subtle, because if a bibliographic tree is transcluded, we do not want its contributors to be included.</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\query/contributors[x]{
 \open\query
 \union-fam-rel{
  \isect{
   \transclusion-coslice{\x}
  }{
   \compl{
    \taxon{reference}
   }
  }
 }{\edges}{\outgoing}{\rel/contributors}
}]]></fr:pre></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:p>In the future, the support for query-indexed families of queries might be generalised to allow arbitrary queries in the components rather than only relational ones. The current version of the feature should be viewed as somewhat provisional.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
